g.text: A number line provides a visual and intuitive way to understand addition.

ul.li: Locate the first number on the number line.
Move to the right by the number of units indicated by the second number.
The final position is the sum.
Move right by the second number.
From the new position, move right by the third number.
Continue until all numbers are added.
Start at 5, move 3 units right to 8.
Start at 4, move 9 units right to 13.
Start at 7, move 11 units right to 18.
A number line visually represents addition as movement to the right.
Adding two numbers: Start at the first number, move right by the second number.
Adding multiple numbers: Continue moving right for each number.
